<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4538659>
    dc:description "FIG. 15. — A, Comtia bernardi Vianey-Liaud, n. gen., n. sp., right M1-2, from Saint-Privat-des-Vieux (Gard; Lower Chattian, MP 26), SPV190, occlusal view; B-D,? cf. Aplodontidae indet. B, SPV187, anterior fragment of lower molar: B1, occlusal, B2, mesial, B3, lin- gual,B4, distal, B5, labial;C, SPV188,posterior? fragment of lower molar: C1, occlusal,C2, mesial,C3, lingual,C4, distal;D, SPV189, fragment of upper tooth: D1, occlusal, D2, lingual, D3, labial, D4, distal. Scale bars: A, 1.5 mm; B-D, 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4538659/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

